com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution

Interface DeviceExecutor.Context

  • Enclosing class:
    DeviceExecutor

    public static interface DeviceExecutor.Context
    Implemented by the DeviceExecutor's owner to abstract from the concrete owning class. The DeviceExecutor.Context is supposed to represent the DeviceExecutor's only way to interact with its world.

      • getDeviceName

        String getDeviceName()

      • createNewObserver

        SunriseConditionObserver createNewObserver(com.kuka.condition.ICondition condition,
                                           NotificationType notificationType,
                                           IConditionListener edgeListener,
                                           IContainerStateListener containerStateListener,
                                           boolean isEnabledOnStart)
        Creates a new SunriseConditionObserver. The DeviceExecutor guarantees that SunriseConditionObserver.dispose() is eventually called.
        Parameters:
        condition - The condition for the observer.
        notificationType - The notification type, on which the condition should react
        edgeListener - The EdgeListener which implements the callback-functions.
        containerStateListener - The ContainerListener to monitor the execution of the SPR.
        isEnabledOnStart - The initial state of the condition observer (enabled or disabled)
        Returns:
        A new SunriseConditionObserver. The DeviceExecutor guarantees that SunriseConditionObserver.dispose() is eventually called.
